Why your “twist” framing is powerful

A twist is essentially a change in structure relative to a baseline.

Information theory describes the same idea:
	•	If nothing changes → no information.
	•	If something deviates from expectation → signal appears.

So communication is always:

baseline medium + structured deviation

Wind becomes speech when you twist it in a meaningful way.

Light becomes writing when you twist its reflection pattern.

Electric current becomes software when you twist voltage states.

